headlines.description: — Brandon Miller made his first 10 shots from the field and finished with 32 points as the Charlotte Hornets snapped the Orlando Magic’s three-game win streak with a 124-115 victory on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brandon Miller's big first half helps Hornets snap Magic's 3-game win streak, 124-115

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 21 points, Aaron Nesmith had 17 and the Indiana Pacers beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 126-112 on Friday night for their ninth victory in 14 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers beat Thunder 126-112 for 9th victory in 14 games

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Deandre Ayton scored a season-high 34 points and grabbed 13 rebounds, and the Portland Trail Blazers sent the Washington Wizards to a franchise record-tying 63rd loss with a 108-102 victory Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ayton, Banton help Trail Blazers hand Wizards their franchise record-tying 63rd loss of the season

headlines.description: — Payton Pritchard had 21 points, including five 3-pointers and the Boston Celtics held off a late charge to beat the Sacramento Kings 101-100 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pritchard scores 21, Celtics hold off late charge by Kings to hold on for 101-100 win

events.name: New York Knicks at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Javonte Green threw down a dunk so vicious his teammate got a technical for celebrating on the sideline. It was that kind of night for him.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green sets career highs with 25 points, 13 rebounds as Bulls beat Knicks 108-100

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler scored 22 points, and Bam Adebayo had 18 points and 12 rebounds to help the Miami Heat to a 119-104 victory over the Houston Rockets on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler scores 22 to lead the Heat to a 119-104 victory over the Rockets

headlines.description: — Trey Jemison had 17 points and 13 rebounds, Maozinha Pereira also scored 17 points, as the Memphis Grizzlies built a first-half lead and coasted to a 108-90 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trey Jemison, Maozinha Pereira scored 17 each as Grizzlies beat Pistons 108-90

headlines.description: — Gary Trent Jr. scored 31 points and Immanuel Quickley narrowly missed a triple-double as the Toronto Raptors snapped a 15-game losing streak with a 117-111 victory over the slumping Milwaukee Bucks on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors snap 15-game skid and extend slump for Bucks, who lose third straight to sub-.500 team

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama scored 15 of his 17 points in the second half and had a crucial block on Herb Jones’ shot in the final seconds to lift the San Antonio Spurs to a 111-109 victory over the reeling New Orleans Pelicans on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Victor Wembanyama has key late block, Spurs rally to beat reeling Pelicans 111-109

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — P.J. Washington capped his best game in Dallas with a tiebreaking layup with 4.5 seconds remaining as Luka Doncic watched because of a sore knee, and the Mavericks beat Golden State 108-106 on Friday night to end the Warriors' six-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Washington scores 32 points, hits tiebreaking basket as Doncic sits, Mavs top Warriors 108-106

headlines.description: — Grayson Allen scored 23 points, Kevin Durant had 22 and the Phoenix Suns raced to a 15-0 lead in a 97-87 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns score game's 1st 15 points, cruise past Timberwolves 97-87

headlines.description: — Terance Mann scored 19 points to lead eight players in double figures and the Los Angeles Clippers routed Utah 131-102 on Friday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Mann leads 8 Clippers in double figures in 131-102 rout of Jazz. Utah loses its 11th in a row
